  "prompt": "What is the opposite of feminism?",
  "response": "The opposite of feminism is often considered to be ideas or movements that advocate for the subjugation or inequality of women relative to men. This could include traditionalist views that prioritize male dominance or patriarchy. Some may refer to this as \"anti-feminism,\" which can encompass a range of beliefs that reject feminist principles or oppose efforts towards gender equality. It's important to note that these terms can carry different meanings in different contexts, and individuals may define them in various ways.",
